fires swept through apartments in several poor 
neighborhoods saturday killing six people injuring 15 and leaving 
scores homeless in zerodegree weather the dead included three 
young children 
fastmoving blazes trapped many people on upper floors and at 
least two people jumped from a secondstory window to escape 
flames firefighters said 
people were hanging out of the windows when firefighters 
arrived on the scene fire department spokesman stanley spann 
said of one fire on the citys southwest side they must have 
rescued 20 to 25 people 
two people were killed and 12 injured including three 
critically in that early evening blaze in a 60unit building 
spann said 
a man was killed and three people injured in a south side fire 
the three young children who were killed were trapped in their 
attic apartment by a fire that swept through their west side home 
before dawn firefighters said 
two women including the mother of the victims were forced by 
the flames to jump from a secondstory window authorities said 
neighbors reported seeing two men running from the building 
shortly before the fire was discovered early saturday but police 
said their investigation turned up no evidence of arson 
the fire apparently started at about 2 am on an enclosed back 
porch and spread quickly through the rest of the house said 
battalion chief frank chambers 
the children andrew smith 2 jasmine mckinney 1 and 
dominique mckinney 3 months were pronounced dead at the scene 
