headquarters of the north atlantic treaty organization for talks 
with nato secretary general manfred woerner and the ambassadors of 
the member nations 
officials have said there is no fixed agenda for the talks at 
alliance headquarters and have described it as a courtesy call that 
is indicative of the new eastwest climate 
on monday shevardnadze will meet with the foreign ministers of 
the 12nation ec trade bloc and sign a cooperation agreement 
he also will meet separately with belgian prime minister 
wilfried martens and king baudouin and will discuss the reforms 
sweeping acrosss eastern europe with government ministers during a 
meeting that will continue over lunch 
the economic agreement with the ec was concluded nov 27 and 
provides for a gradual lifting of ec import quotas on soviet 
industrial goods by 1995 
the accord also lists a dozen areas in which the ec and the 
soviet union plan to establish economic cooperation these include 
science and technology banking transport agriculture 
environmental protection energy raw materials and mining 
the accord excludes trade in goods that are considered 
militarily sensitive according to ec sources 
the ecsoviet accord is the fourth between the community and an 
east european nation since the ec and the moscowled comecon trade 
bloc signed a mutual recognition accord june 25 1988 
since then the ec has concluded trade and economic cooperation 
accords with the soviet union hungary poland and czechoslovakia 
the ecs trade with eastern europe is small it totalled only 
56 billion in 1987 the last year for which complete figures are 
available and about half of that was with the soviet union 
by comparison the ecs trade with switzerland that year was 
some 66 billion 
