should be legal in certain circumstances fiftythree percent 
said yes in december compared to 51 percent in march 
the random telephone survey by krccommunications research of 
cambridge had a margin of error of plus or minus 3 percent 
on the question of whether public funds should be used for 
abortions for women who cannot afford them 49 percent of the 
december sample said the money should be available and 34 percent 
said it should not be used 
